---
import FeaturePage from '../../layouts/FeaturePage.astro';
---

<FeaturePage
  title="End-to-end Type Safety"
  description="Schema-first codegen. Types flow from the database all the way into your UI."
  badge="Core · Library"
  activePath="/features"
>
  <p>
    Define your schema in SurrealQL once. sp00ky generates matching types for every client
    language, so autocomplete and compile-time checks cover the whole stack. No hand-written
    DTOs, no stale types, no drift between server and client.
  </p>
  <p>
    Rename a field, and every call site that breaks lights up in your IDE before you ship.
    Add a column, and your clients pick it up on the next build.
  </p>
  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Schema lives in SurrealQL files, versioned with your code.</li>
    <li>Codegen emits types for TypeScript, Dart, Rust, and more.</li>
    <li>Queries, mutations, and reactive subscriptions are all typed.</li>
    <li>Migrations are schema-aware, so breaking changes surface in CI.</li>
  </ul>
</FeaturePage>
